Method Replacement
------------------

mandatory = medical insurance policy (1200$ per family (#4)) = 40% earnings 

USA government = issues medical insurance policies to below poverty line people (below $65k, the govt itself provides medical insurance policies)
	
insurance providers/payers (health insurance policies) [$1200 per month an average]
1. uhg
2. atena
3. wellpoint
4. metlife

minimum benefits (governing) :
policies

1. cashless facility: Yes
2. in-patient: admitted and stayed more than 24 hours by allocating a bed
3. out-patient: doctor visit
4. copay      : 10%, 20%, 30% of the expense incurred. 1 lac = 80k coverage medical insurance provider, 20k 
5. cap amount: 5 lacs

open enrollment period = Nov - Jan [30 cr ] [90 days]
Biggest market for insurance provider: Nov - Jan

digital platforms: web applications and mobile applications (self enrollment)
digital tools (AI/Decision-Based Systems): Find Plans


	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	



















































	

